Description:
Ballistics of 115x728R 3UBM5 round, with the 3BM6 steel core APFSDS-T shot, fired from the U-5TS tank gun (GRAU index 2A20), chiefly employed on the T-62 tank. 

Barrel Length:      5840 mm
Cartridge Length:    723 mm
Projectile Travel:  5117 mm  (estimated from above)
Peak Pressure:      3650 kgf/cm² space-mean pressure
Muzzle Velocity:    1600 m/s 
Chambrage:          1.37     from 枪炮内弹道学 (2014).
Propellant: 
Mass      Propellant  Geometry   Web      Perf Diam.  Force (from "545")
1.1   kg  Pyroxylin   18/1-37.5  1.73 mm  1.89 mm     830,000 kgf-dm/kg
2.1   kg  Pyroxylin   18/1-28.5  1.73 mm  1.88 mm     830,000 kgf-dm/kg
4.734 kg  Pyroxylin   12/7       1.27 mm  0.44 mm     900,000 kgf-dm/kg

Chinese chemical analysis from captured example (vehicle T-62 №545) indicates propellant is of relatively low force, although this is not specifically mentioned in Soviet documentation
